release_note: Muse is your calm space for deep thinking. Thanks for all of your feedback! The improvements included in this version: Reduced memory consumption when rendering snapshots Small fixes to reduce rare crashes during snapshots Updated snapshot rendering to latest iOS frameworks Fixed memory leak when navigating between boards Fixes old tweet metadata import that could cause general performance issues Improved fetching URL metadata to reduce lag

The improvements included in this version: Fixes the Edit Title icon in the card s context menu Fixes crash on iOS 14 when loading a keyboard toolbar icon Fixes crash when decompressing large images Fixes crash during onboarding for some users

The fixes included in this version: Fixes the Heading style being applied inline to normal text blocks Fixes typing disappearing while typing text blocks and reappearing after finishing Fixes ink being deleted after selecting ink in a PDF page and then navigating out before deselecting

Muse is your calm space for deep thinking. Thanks for all of your feedback! The fixes included in this version: Pinch gesture preferences are now in UI Customization settings instead of Backstage Pass Fixes infinite beachball when choosing some results from Search Fixes some boards not allowing pinch to zoom out if the content is nearly the size of the screen Fix crash when opening some search results Fix exported large boards as PDFs not including links for URL cards and incorrect locations of card connections Performance fixes when syncing after wake Performance fix related to card snapshots

Lots of fixes and new features in this build thanks for your support and feedback! Cmd Shift Enter from search results will open with correct breadcrumbs iPads can now hide show the pencil tools button in the toolbar in Settings UI Customization can always use Pencil to swipe in from side Fixes lag when typing long Notes or Text Blocks Fix some files getting stuck while syncing New tabs windows don t show the title of the document PDFs with rotated pages often landscape pages will now export their ink correctly Pasting URLs in iOS will add card to top of inbox Window tab titles correctly show document title when opening new documents from search Fixed rare crash when downloading file completes Fixes some sync issues with files images pdfs Toolkit will hug edge of screen when opened from toolbar UI is hidden First letter of edited title is in wrong font General performance improvements

Fixes crash caused by bug in logging library Fix crash when showing the backstage pass tooltip in the sidebar Fix crash from documentation tooltip when sidebar is closed Fix incorrect warning message when removing collaborator Start with empty text field when clicking Untitled Workspace in navigation bar

Backstage Pass is back! Members can choose the gesture to use for zooming a board and navigating into and out of boards. Customized gestures will be released to all users soon. Fix for deleted connections sometime rendering in snapshots and exports Fix for rare crash during logging Fix for launching into safe mode manually with URL when 2.x 3.0 migration is needed

Thanks for all of your support! This update contains a number of important fixes particularly for those seeing the workspaces don t sync bug. Also pencil toolkit is now accessible from the Mac. The full list of changes since 3.0.1: open pencil ink toolkit from toolbar pencil button on iPad and Mac fixes workspaces not always syncing between devices fixes disappearing ink when zooming out a lot fixes possible deadlock when reloading list of user s workspaces fixes infrequent crash when reloading sidebar fixes main thread crash when an invitation arrives after clicking link from email fixes workspace menu to refresh properly after leaving a workspace fixes repeat delayed network traffic after leaving a workspace fixes rare crash when calculating default scroll position of a board tapping to hide interface now also hides the sidebar fixes UI jump updates iPhone error message to mention enabling iCloud Drive specifically

Muse 3 is here with an all new UI collaborative workspaces zoom new pricing and much more. Collaborative workspaces Workspaces: Create multiple Muse workspaces and switch between them with the workspace switcher in the new sidebar upgrade to a paid membership for more workspaces Collaboration: Add collaborators to a Muse workspace to work together on Muse boards upgrade to a paid membership for more collaborators per workspace Collaboration features: Muse 3 adds many collaboration based features like online status live cursors following click on the avatar of another user to follow them board presence user avatars show up on the board that they are in and comments add them through the new toolbar UI features Redesigned interface: Muse now has a persistent navigation bar at the top a toolbar at the bottom and an optional sidebar showing linked cards and other features. Breadcrumb navigation: The new navigation bar shows you the full path of your current board and lets you navigate easily. Back forward navigation: The new navigation bar lets you navigate back and forward between boards as you would in a web browser. Zoom: Muse boards can now be zoomed out just by pinching. Muse is now fully functional while zoomed out including selections. This replaces the board overview feature as well as the pinch gesture to open or close boards. UI customization: On iPad you can now activate two gestures for advanced users in Settings: A 3 finger swipe to close boards and a tap on the canvas to hide the UI. New tools Search: Find and open boards based on their title or any text within them. Search is accessible through the sidebar. Card connections: A new tool in the toolbar lets you select two cards and connects them with a line that moves along with the cards. Ink on Mac: The toolbar also brings the ink tool from the iPad to the Mac. Click the arrow next to it to switch between pen highlighter presenter pen and eraser. Templates: We have added a first batch of pre made templates to the toolbar focused around team workflows. Copy URL: The share menu in the navigation bar now has an option to copy the URL to the current board. Anyone with Muse installed who is a collaborator in the workspace will be able to open the board through the URL. Selections: Cards can now be added to or removed from a selection by holding CMD or Shift while creating another rectangle selection. Onboarding: New users will see a short series of guided onboarding instructions to help them get started. Formatting features: Colored cards and text headings are now available for all users previously only for paid members Pricing New Pro membership: The previous Starter plan has been upgraded to the new Pro plan and now has unlimited cards and larger maximum board sizes while supporting up to 10 workspaces with 5 collaborators each. New Unlimited membership: The previous Pro plan has been upgraded to the new Unlimited plan and now has unlimited workspaces and collaborators as well as other supporter benefits.

We are working on Muse for Teams a shared workspace for your team to think collaboratively. To get a sneak peek and be one of the first to try it header over to museapp.com teams This update includes bug fixes and small improvements.

New Turn into Note feature: Add structure to your inking and turn it into movable cards. Just select any ink then turn it into a note card through the selection menu. Our Muse community is now open to everyone. Join the Discord at museapp.com community Bug fixes and improvements: Text blocks no longer count towards the card limit for users on the Free or Starter plan Improved performance when pasting multiple paragraphs of text Tweaked padding for Move to New Board feature to avoid board title overlap Other small bug fixes

New Move to New Board feature: Want to reorganize your board or make space for something new Now you can move selected content into a new board through the selection menu or with Shift CMD B. Bug fixes and improvements: Dialed down the snapping behavior of text blocks Fixes ink not being visible in board overview for large boards Fixes a bug where the board title would reset when entering one very shortly after creating the board Other small bug fixes

Our holiday update makes linked cards available to all users adds colors and a heading format to text blocks for Pro users and fixes a number of bugs. Linked cards are now out of beta and available for all users: Linked cards are a powerful new way of navigating and organizing your Muse content. They are copies of a card which point to the same document. Use the card menu of a board card note card image card or PDF card to add a linked card. Linked cards are indicated by an icon in the top left. Tap it to see all other linked cards that point to the same document. Learn more at museapp.com linkedcards New text block formatting options available for Pro users: Long pressing a text block will now reveal a context menu. Set colors for text blocks just like you can with other cards. Requires turning on Card colors in the Backstage Pass panel. Turn text blocks into headings with the Format option in the new text block context menu or with the formatting buttons in the keyboard bar. Requires turning on Text headings in the Backstage Pass panel. Soon we will add more formatting options for text blocks. On Mac text blocks now show their border only when hovering over their group. On iPad the border is still shown at all times. Bug fixes and improvements: iPadOS 16 users will see a more compact layout for card menus Sharing a screenshot directly to Muse works again
Improved onboarding for Muse on iPhone Bug fixes and small improvements
Bug fixes and performance improvements

New board card resize behavior: Board cards now keep their size even as you add or move content. You can now freely resize board cards no longer locked to an aspect ratio and the board preview will automatically adapt to fill the card sensibly. This replaces the previous crop functionality which made you drag the edges of the board card. An indicator in the bottom right of a board card is visible if the board card has empty space or if the board preview is cropped. Tap the indicator to immediately shrink the size of the board card to fit its content. Card colors available only for Pro members : Use the card menu to choose a color for your board cards note cards and link cards. Available only for Pro members through the Backstage Pass the star icon in the action bar .

Our Muse Discord community is now open to all Pro members through the Backstage Pass. In rare cases where cards got stuck outside the canvas of a board those cards are now moved back to the top left corner of the canvas. Other bug fixes and performance improvements

See your whole board at once with the new board overview feature. On boards larger than your screen a new button will appear in the bottom left on iPad. Tap or hold it to enter board overview then tap anywhere to zoom back in. You can also use the keyboard shortcut CMD O to toggle board overview. On Mac board overview is available from the menu bar in the View menu. Other improvements: More precise zoom in when navigating into a board by tapping or pinching on a specific spot of the board card Fixed an issue where the sync status detail view would behave erratically while syncing large amounts of data Other small bug fixes

Introducing linked cards now available as a beta for Pro members in the Backstage Pass. Linked cards let you transclude content create shortcuts and experience a new way of navigating your boards with location switching our take on backlinks. If you re a Pro member you can opt into linked cards in your Backstage Pass the star icon in the action bar .
Additional ink performance improvements

Some users who were unable to use sync will see a prompt to login again in the Settings panel. Other bug fixes and small improvements

Undo redo is available per board and no longer resets when navigating. Various bug fixes and improvements.

The Pencil toolkit now appears whenever you tap to open the action bar. You can also still swipe it in with the Pencil from any edge of the screen. Improved performance while inking or erasing on boards. Other bug fixes and improvements Changed keyboard shortcuts: CMD E to excerpt selected content from a PDF or image Shift CMD I to move selected cards to the inbox Shift CMD N to open a new window

Muse 2 for Mac and iPad is now available in beta to all of our Pro members. Check your Backstage Pass panel for installation instructions.
Bug fixes and improvements
Small bugfixes and improvements

Export boards as images: The export panel has a new option to share boards as PNGs. Copying or dragging boards into other apps will now insert an image instead of a PDF. Other improvements: Relaunching Muse will more reliably restore your previously open windows Further improvements to pointer support

Improved pointer support: When using Muse with a mouse or trackpad the pointer will now react when hovering over important interactive elements. Click and drag the pointer over content to select everything within the rectangle. Right click on a card to open the card menu. Fixes multiple small bugs around pointer interactions.

Card menu: Tap the ellipsis in the top right of a card to open the new card menu. Use it to quickly share copy or duplicate the card and to view content in Split View with a single tap. Other improvements: Tweaked look of the Source Peek indicator on cards Small bug fixes and improvements
Fixes a crash when customizing the pencil toolkit.

Drag cards to other apps: Touch and hold a card or selection until it lifts up then drag it to another app to copy it there. This works best if you have Muse open side by side with another app in Split View or Slide Over. Drag cards to a Split View or Slide Over window: Lift up a card as described above then drag it to the left or right edge of the screen to open it in a new Muse window in Split View or Slide Over. You can move cards between Muse windows the same way. Other improvements: Fixes a syncing issue with the iPhone app
Fixes an issue with downloading data from the browser extension.
Multi window: You can now use the Dock to open a second Muse window in Split View. Each window can navigate through your Muse boards independently.

Backstage pass: The new Muse Backstage Pass provides early access to new features. Only available for Pro members who can access it through a new button in the action bar. Text blocks: Block based text editing is the first beta feature available through the Backstage Pass. It s our first step for more powerful text editing in Muse and we rely on your feedback to develop it further. Other improvements: An improved login page provides more information about Muse for new users before entering their email address. Login code emails are delivered more reliably and faster. Performance improvements when moving cards on boards with a lot of ink. Many small bug fixes.

Updated board cards: Board cards will now take on the shape of their content grow with it resulting in more diverse and personal board layouts. Drag the right or bottom edge of such a board card to crop it making it keep its size even as you add content. New membership pricing options: We are introducing a cheaper Starter membership with limited cards and smaller board size. Both membership plans now have a monthly payment option.

Duplicating a selection will now also duplicate ink.
New membership purchase dialog including an expanded FAQ and customer quotes.

System copy paste of selections including keyboard shortcuts Bug fixes: Fixed ink blurriness on PDFs and images Fixes undoing erase taking several undos Fixes bugs with moving ink selections that are being dropped on views different from the source of the selection Allows excerpting of ink on PDF after the selection has been moved to another page
Small bug fixes and improvements
Fixes a bug where dragging a card into the inbox would create a duplicate card

Introduces the presenter pen a new Pencil tool. Ink drawn with the presenter pen disappears after a few seconds. Perfect for drawing attention and sketching while showing your content to others. You can add the presenter pen to your toolkit in the Settings panel.
Various fixes and improvements
Ink sticks to cards when the ink stroke is completely inside the card s border.
Fixes a crash when processing a purchase of the in app subscription
Fixes some subscriptions not correctly appearing as renewed
New YouTube links will correctly show the video s title Fixes a crash with animated GIF cards

Introduces flex boards allowing you to expand boards both horizontally and vertically! When the iPad is in portrait orientation Muse now uses the full screen instead of showing a black bar at the bottom.
New: Move selected ink between boards and other cards Inking on fullscreen text now works properly in portrait orientation Other fixes and performance improvements
You can now move ink between PDF pages. Prepares your inking data for upcoming features. Fixes a bug when moving selected ink outside the screen edges
This version prepares your Muse database for upcoming features.
Fixes a crash in the iPhone app and rare crash in iPad app
Fixed a crash caused by importing very large files Reduced overall memory consumption Added a safe mode to allow extracting data if the app experiences recurring crashes
You can now export your boards as navigable PDFs that will include all sub boards as separate pages.
Bugfixes Improvements
Fixes a crash caused by corrupt memory when viewing PDFs

More consistently load the last viewed document when relaunching Muse. Relaunch into individual PDF pages when appropriate. Last used tool will be initially selected when relaunching. Fixes Fixed a rare crash caused when using the selection tool. Reduced memory usage resulting in fewer memory related crashes.

Significant stability improvements particularly for large files and PDFs Import .webloc files as URL cards Fix for importing many files at the same time sometimes skipping files Ink smoothing adjustments

You can now customize your Pencil Toolkit. Add pens and highlighters with new colors and widths expand the number of tools reorder them or remove tools you don t need. See Pencil Toolkit in Settings. Tools in positions 1 2 and 3 in your Toolkit will now be activated by pressing 1 2 or 3 fingers down respectively. When activated in this way the Toolkit now highlights the tool. When swiping in the Toolkit from the edge of the screen dragging the Pencil far enough will now select the last active tool. The Toolkit has a new visual design. Block selection is triggered at a slightly higher Pencil angle to make it easier to activate. Bug fixes: Improved reliability of Scribble feature.
iOS 14 support! Use Scribble to create new text cards with your handwriting! Various tweaks and bug fixes
iOS 14 support! Use Scribble to create new text cards with your handwriting! Various tweaks and bug fixes
Fixed a bug where dropping cards on a board sometimes places them behind other cards.

Add support for animated GIFs Add ability to recover deleted cards Pressing the escape key now zooms out a level or drops the focus of a text card if one is currently active Show a spinner while generating PDFs for export Add ability to export debugging information to Muse developers Various bug fixes

PDFs save position when you zoom out and last read page shows a bookmark icon Large cards will no longer fully cover and hide smaller cards System setting for Pencil taps will let you quickly show hide the tool palette or switch between tools Various bugs and fixes
Bug Fixes crash when importing audio file other bug fixes and tweaks

Import Twitter URLs into tweet cards including attached links and images Import your videos into playable video cards Bug fix: pen marker and highlighter width for PDF excerpts
A visual refresh including higher contrast boards and more prominent labels Onboarding improvements for new users Lots of smaller improvements and bugfixes
Smoother ink New App Store text and screenshots
Add a 4th custom pen! Add ability to drag drop arbitrary files into Muse Add ability to Airdrop files into Muse Bug Fixes Fixes rare crash when inking Various small formatting fixes
Small changes and bug fixes

Added single tap to zoom into cards Images and PDFs can now have labels Arbitrary files can be added as cards onto a board Context menu for selections allows duplicating cards Memory optimizations particularly when caused by lots of ink Bug Fixes: Fixes being unable to pinch out of a PDF page after double tapping to view

Added single tap to zoom into cards Images and PDFs can now have labels Arbitrary files can be added as cards onto a board Context menu for selections allows duplicating cards Memory optimizations particularly when caused by lots of ink
Fixes a bug affecting dragging a selection of cards

You can now view the source document for excerpts from PDFs and images. Tap and hold the circle in the bottom left corner of an excerpt card to peek at the source. Pinching into the source will get you to the full document. Bug fixes: Fix an issue where swiping while a PDF was scrolling would incorrectly slow the scroll. Fix an issue where selections were being deselected when tilting the iPad Fix an issue where selections would jump to a wrong location after being moved on a scrolled board

Lasso selections are now available on images and PDFs in addition to the previous block option. Creating an excerpt from a lasso selection makes a non rectangular excerpt. The type of selection is determined by the grip of the Pencil and the resulting angle of the Pencil to the iPad. A low angle grip makes a block selection a regular grip a lasso selection. These two types of selections are also available on boards in the same way.

Selections can now also be moved with this Pencil. Whereas a finger in a selection moves ink cards on boards or creates an excerpt on images and PDFs the Pencil always moves only ink. Excerpt cards are now heuristically downsized when placed in the inbox so that their size is better when placed on boards. Bug fixes: Fix PDF view sometimes scrolling after dragging an excerpt. Correct issue with excerpts sometimes containing the wrong content.
Bug fixes: Address memory issues that caused crashes on certain complex boards.

You can now create excerpts from images and PDFs: select a portion of the source with the selection tool then drag with your finger from within that selection to the inbox. Bug fixes: Allow small selections that previously got auto cancelled. Avoid flashing recently erased ink if the Pencil is briefly lifted during an erase stroke. When sharing an item to Muse that has multiple representations only create a single card in Muse for the richest representation. When indicating successful sharing of an item to Muse only show the left most part of the home board if that board has been expanded to avoid distortion.

New login flow uses automatically emailed login links instead of manually sent access codes Bug fixes: Undoing the move of a selection containing both ink and cards now undoes all of those moves in one action instead of requiring an undo for each individual move Don t auto complete selections to tiny areas Only allow selections with two fingers down on boards Include ink on PDF exports Correctly update the iOS search index when a board s title is removed or changed Fix crashes on imports of bundles with many URL cards

You can now select ink and cards on a board with the selection tool available from the tool switcher The selection tool can also be invoked by holding down two fingers while using the Pencil Once selected content can be moved within a board or deleted by flicking it off the edge The erase tool is now available in the tool switcher too in addition to the existing method of holding down one finger while using the Pencil Bug fixes: Undo redo taps are better disambiguated from finger presses to temporarily switch between Pencil tools Stopping a scrolling board with two fingers will no longer trigger an undo Fixed issue with hiding and showing card titles when cards are overlapping

Expanding a board can be undone. We created a handbook to help you learn how to use Muse. You can access it through the settings panel. Bug fixes: Enable resizing of very narrow images. Fix ink on scrollable text. Fix layout of smaller boards imported into larger devices.

Settings panel to see your membership status and access useful links user settings will also be added here in the future. Undo button allows faster repeated taps. Action bar buttons can be tapped with the Pencil. Bug fixes: Include ink annotations in exported images. Fix some issues with eraser not erasing as expected.
